<HEADLINE>
QUITE A CATCH FOR TROJANS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC received an important commitment to shore up
its wide-receiver position Sunday when high school All-American
Steve Stevenson said he will play for the Trojans next season.
</P>
<P>
   Stevenson, of Charter Oak High in Covina, selected USC over
UCLA, Colorado, Oregon and Texas A&AMP;M. He caught 34 passes for 630
yards and 10 touchdowns while rushing for more than 600 yards and
17 touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   Stevenson is listed as an All-American by several recruiting
services. USC returns just two receivers _ R. Jay Soward and
Windrell Hayes _ who caught a pass last season. Besides Stevenson,
USC has also received a commitment from Long Beach Poly wide
receiver Kareem Kelly.
</P>
<P>
   USC also hosted wide receiver Ronald Bellamy, of Marrero, La.,
who is expected to make a decision this week. Bellamy is
considering USC, Michigan, Ohio State, Kansas State and Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver Marcell Allmond of St. Paul, another All-American,
will visit USC this weekend.
</P>
<P>
   USC also received a commitment from offensive lineman Norman
Katnick (6-foot-3, 225 pounds) from Esperanza High. He is the
nephew of former USC lineman John Katnick.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans also lost a couple recruits recently. Westchester
High's Courtney Morgan, who committed last month, has now said he
will attend Michigan. Quarterback Ken Dorsey of Miramonte High in
Orinda selected Miami over the Trojans on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   USC is also no longer recruiting defensive lineman Malcolm
Woolridge of Boca Raton, Fla. He will not qualify academically and
is expected to attend a prep school next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
