<HEADLINE>
BRAZIL TOPPLES OFF THE VERGE 
</HEADLINE>
 
 (Repeating for all needing.) (The Week in Review) 
(EDS: lyrics in lede should be italicized) 
(bl) 
 By TIMOTHY L. O'BRIEN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Tall and tanned and young and lovely
</P>
<P>
   The girl from Ipanema goes walking
</P>
<P>
   And when she passes
</P>
<P>
   Each one she passes
</P>
<P>
   Goes ``Aaah''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Girl From Ipanema''
</P>
<P>
   Like the sensual strains of that old bossa nova tune, Brazil
enchants. And it has been attracting treasure hunters of all
stripes for centuries.
</P>
<P>
   From the Portuguese who colonized Brazil between 1500 and 1822
to the Wall Street money managers who made the country a darling of
