<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAT-FURNITURE-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE PURRRFECT LINE OF FURNITURE FOR FURRY FRIENDS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By FRANCES INGRAHAM  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ Almost any cat owner will tell you that their
tabby is used to being pampered and is accustomed to the finer
things in life _ from gourmet cat food to a soft place to sleep.
</P>
<P>
   But if you don't allow kitty in bed with you, don't fret. You
can go furniture shopping instead. A trip to most pet stores will
put you in touch with a fun line of bedding for your feline.
</P>
<P>
   There are kitty hammocks starting at around $20. The hammocks
feature a padded plush washable pad that is connected to a metal
form. The suspended bed never gets lumpy or disheveled and the
slight movement is supposed to lull kitty to sleep.
</P>
<P>
   There also are soft sculptures for cats to sleep in, such as a
colorful stuffed fish for $29.99. The bed entrance is through the
large opening of the fish's mouth.
</P>
<P>
   One company, Doskocil Manufacturing of Arlington, Texas, makes a
line of Kat Furniture from Petmate of neutral-colored durable
plastic pieces with plush bedding, designed for various rooms of
the house.
</P>
<P>
   Consider the TV bed for $54.99 for the family room, or the sock
drawer bed and armchair bed in the bedroom. The $69.99 armchair
also could fit in the living room or the kitchen.
</P>
<P>
   There's no need to worry if kitty exercises its claws on this
line of furniture; the chair and sock drawer come with large sisal
scratch surfaces. In addition, replaceable interactive toys (some
filled with catnip) are built into each piece.
</P>
<P>
   The company is making a set of bunk beds to add to its line of
Kat Furniture, which won the top three awards for best new cat
product of 1998 at the recent American Pet Products Manufacturers
Association trade show in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Some assembly with a screwdriver is necessary for Kat Furniture,
which can be found at some pet supply stores.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-18-99 1256EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
