SELECTED FROM BOOKS RECENTLY REVIEWED IN THE GLOBE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
``Careless Love: The Unmaking of Elvis Presley'' by Peter Guralnick
(Little, Brown, $27.95). The decline and fall of a king. 
 
``Elegy for Iris'' by John Bayley (St. Martin's, $22.95). Scenes
from a 42-year love affair and marriage _ before and after the
onset of Alzheimer's disease. 
 
``The Endurance: Shackleton's Legendary Antarctic Expedition'' by
Caroline Alexander (Knopf, $29.95). To hell and back with Sir
Ernest Shackleton's attempt to cross the Antarctic in 1914. 
 
``The House of Rothschild: Money's Prophets, 1798-1848'' by Niall
Ferguson (Viking, $34.95). The epic story of the five brothers who
created a banking empire. 
 
``I Will Bear Witness: A Diary of the Nazi Years, 1933-1941'' by
Victor Klemperer (Random House, $29.95). The extraordinary record
of a German Jew who lived and wrote through a nightmare. 
 
``Amsterdam'' by Ian McEwan (Doubleday, $21). Two Englishmen are
brought together by the death of a lover they shared. Winner of the
1998 Booker Prize.
