</P>
<P>
   WIRED-ALLIANCE (San Francisco) _ Sony, Sun Microsystems and
Philips Electronics, creating a bridge between the consumer
electronics world and the Internet, will announce a plan to tie
together home devices like televisions, stereo receivers and
videocassette recorders with the global computer network. By John
Markoff.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-MARCONI (London) _ Britain's General Electric Co. PLC
and British Aerospace PLC confirmed Monday they are in advanced
discussions, following a published report that they are near a deal
involving GEC's Marconi defense unit. By Alan Cowell.
</P>
<P>
   Eds, the U.S. stock and credit markets are closed Monday for the
Martin Luther King Jr. holiday.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY &LR;  (``k'' code)
</P>
