ART-STAGE (Los Angeles) _ It's a play with Alan Alda and Alfred
Molina but nobody named Art. Molina plays one of three men whose
friendship gets turned on its head when Victor Garber's character
buys a piece of modern art: an all-white painting. By Reed
Johnson. 
. 
