   SKI (Georgetown, Colo.) - Next weekend, skiers here are to
inaugurate the world's highest chair lift, but in a sign of
changing times in the nation's most popular skiing state, a
Colorado environmentalist is suing. After fighting logging, mining
and cattle grazing on National Forest lands, environmentalists
declared open season this winter on ski areas, once the
environmental good guys. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ATLANTA (Atlanta) _ Fans used to winning, fans in cities
where teams routinely make a realistic run for the NFL
championship, might not understand Atlanta's quiet reaction to
winning, but many Falcons fans had to recover from the shock before
they could whoop and stomp. By Rick Bragg.
