her that I, too, was a teacher, wasn't feeling well and might kill
her first if she didn't have the decency to let me sit for a
minute. She cocked her head. ``Whatever,'' she said, and went back
to her homework.
</P>
<P>
   _JUDITH NICHTERN
</P>
