<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: WHAT THE DRESS SHOE LEARNED
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Finally, here come fashionable shoes designed to be
comfortable. The innovation combines the technology of athletic
shoes with the styling of dress shoes. Molded bottoms of rubberized
synthetic materials that conform to the contours of the foot are
combined with uppers of leather or fabric, resulting in shoes that
are dressy enough to be worn at the office, and maybe even out to
dinner.
</P>
<P>
   Bloomingdale's has fabric-upper Mary Janes by Report ($40 and
$49) and David Aaron ($98); skimmers with leather uppers by BCBG
($110) and Donna Karan ($295), and leather loafers by CK Calvin
Klein ($98) and Stephane Kelian ($270).
</P>
<P>
   Prada's ergonomic styles include scuba booties ($320), Mary
Janes ($250), moccasins ($270), penny loafers ($270) and slides
($220). Neiman Marcus has all the Prada shoes, as well as slides by
Donna Karan ($275) and Gucci ($175) and a sportier lug-soled sandal
by Chanel ($395).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
