   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-U.S. (Washington) _ Scoffing at warnings by the Clinton
administration that he must comply with a ceasefire in Kosovo, the
Yugoslav leader, Slobodan Milosevic, orders a top U.S. diplomat out
of Kosovo and refuses entry to a U.N. war crimes prosecutor who
arrived at the province's border to investigate a massacre. By Jane
Perlez. (We plan to move the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news
file.)
