   INSIDE STORIES PROMOTED ON PAGE 1:
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-CHILDCARE (Washington) _ President Clinton will embrace
an idea long favored by conservatives and propose a tax break for
parents who stay home to care for their children, White House
officials say. By Robert Pear. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET in
``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-AIDS-THERAPY (San Diego) _ In a bold but potentially
frightening effort to turn one of the world's most virulent killers
into a cure, scientists and biotechnology companies are trying to
tame the AIDS virus and harness it to treat disease. By Andrew
Pollack. (The story has moved in ``a'' news file.) With photo.
2,050 words.
</P>
