<P>
   PHONES-COMPETE (Undated) _ It's hard being a regional Bell these
days. Just ask executives at Bell Atlantic Corp. on Monday after
finishing second with their bid to acquire Airtouch Communications
Inc. Instead of creating the world's largest wireless
communications carrier with a strong base in the Northeast, they
watched Airtouch announce at a news conference in London that it
was joining forces with Vodafone Group PLC, Britain's biggest
wireless company. A news analysis. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom)
</P>
<P>
   BELO-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ It's as if, as 1998 ended, some
prankster turned A.H. Belo Corp.'s stock chart upside down. Falling
from $28 and change to less than $20 last year, a stock that had
long paced the newspaper industry fell far behind, with its worst
performance since Belo went public in 1981. A quarterly earnings
report due on Thursday will show whether Belo's efforts to control
expenses in the last six months have had results. By Allen R.
Myerson and Felicity Barringer.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
