</HEADLINE>
  
 ``NEGROPONTE'S IDEAS for the MILLENNIUM'': Readers Ask About the
21st Century's Major People and Products; Reinventing the
20th-Century Mall; and Overcoming Technophobia  
 &HT;     (This has already moved to clients of Nicholas Negroponte's
monthly column. To purchase as a one-shot, please contact one of
these New York Times Syndicate sales representatives: 
 &HT;    (--U.S. and Canada: DEBRA WEYDERT in New Jersey at
1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697. 
 &HT;    (--Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942. 
 &HT;    (--Latin America: OLIVIA VASQUEZ in Los Angeles, 310-798-0970;
fax, 310-798-7338.)  By NICHOLAS NEGROPONTE  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
