<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, JANUARY 19
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-EXCLUSIVE-CUBA-REBELS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Jan. 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Jan. 14,
about five Central Americans accused of having carried out a
bombing campaign in Cuba two years ago misstated the time of a
regional summit meeting in Venezuela where United States
prosecutors say a group of Cuban exiles planned to assassinate
Fidel Castro. It was in November 1997, not May 1998.
</P>
<P>
   BC-FBN-ARATON-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Sunday, Jan. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Jan. 17,
about John Elway of the Denver Broncos and his performance against
the Jets in the American Conference championship game misidentified
the receiver who caught the touchdown pass from Elway. He was
Howard Griffith, not Dwayne Carswell.
</P>
