<HEADLINE>
UCLA GETS TOP LINEBACKER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ San Jose's Marcus Reese, the state's No. 1-rated
linebacker, gave UCLA an oral commitment. He is 6-2, 210 pounds and
attends Oak Grove High School, which produced UCLA's senior tight
end, Mike Grieb.
</P>
<P>
   Reese chose UCLA over Cal and Tennessee and has a chance to play
next season. The Bruins have just five experienced linebacker:
Santi Hall, Robert Thomas, Ryan Nece, Tony White and Ramogi Huma.
</P>
</TEXT>
