IMPEACHMENT TRIAL SCHEDULE FOR TUESDAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (See also IMPEACH-RDP, IMPEACH-SANTORUM, IMPEACH-LOBBY) 
(nk) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
  
  Following is the expected schedule for the impeachment trial of
President Clinton:
<TEXT>
<P>
   TUESDAY
</P>
<P>
   1 p.m. _ &UR;  &LR; Clinton's lawyers begin their presentation.
</P>
<P>
   LATER
</P>
<P>
   Senators question parties and debate motions to dismiss the case
and to subpoena witnesses. They vote on dismissal. If that is
defeated, they will vote on witnesses.
</P>
