u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBO-SOSA-DINNER-NYT &LR;      01-18 0314
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBO-SOSA-DINNER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOSA SKIPS A DINNER THAT WAS TO HONOR HIM 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Ill., Nev., Calif.) (DUPLICATION NOTICE: Also filed in category ``s'') (nk) 
 By IRA BERKOW   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Sammy Sosa, the Chicago Cubs slugger who with Mark
McGwire electrified the baseball world last season, was a no-show
at Monday night's Congress of Racial Equality dinner at which he
was to be honored.
</P>
<P>
   Organizers said that Sosa had agreed several weeks ago to attend
the event, a fund-raiser for CORE, on the national holiday
celebrating the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. and that they expected
until the last minute that he would attend. About 2,500 people did
attend, including Sen. Charles Schumer and Mayor Rudolph Giuliani.
</P>
<P>
   Mel A. Sachs, the general counsel for CORE, said Sosa's
appearance had been confirmed three times, but then ``they kept
making more and more demands, until we were just unable _ and
unwilling _ to meet them.''
</P>
<P>
   According to Roy Innis, national chairman of CORE, the
organization had agreed to provide Sosa with first-class airline
tickets from his home in Santo Domingo, the Dominican Republic, to
New York and back, a limousine in New York and a double hotel
suite. Innis said that the requests from Sosa's representatives
then began to increase, including a private jet to the Mike Tyson
fight in Las Vegas, then to New York and back to the Dominican
Republic. Innis said requests were also made for $50,000 in
contributions and an auction of Sosa memorabilia, all for Sosa's
charity in the Dominican Republic.
</P>
<P>
   Innis added that two first-class round-trip plane tickets for
Sosa in the Santo Domingo airport had not been picked up.
</P>
<P>
   Adam Katz, Sosa's representative in Los Angeles, said that the
CORE statements about the Sosa negotiations were inaccurate and ``a
distortion.'' He would not comment further.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-18-99 2329EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
