<HEADLINE>
FINES SOUGHT AGAINST HEALTH CLUB OVER REFUSALS TO CANCEL
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 By MONTE WILLIAMS   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The City Department of Consumer Affairs is seeking
$150,000 in fines against the Lucille Roberts health club chain
because of complaints from members who had been refused legitimate
refunds or who had not been allowed to cancel memberships,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Consumer Affairs Commissioner Jules Polonetsky said Monday that
the chain, which has branches throughout the city, would face an
administrative law judge in the agency's adjudication unit on Jan.
28 to answer 19 complaints, half of all the agency's current
complaints against health clubs in New York City.
</P>
<P>
   One member, Veronica Latourette-Andrade, 28, of Brooklyn found
that Lucille Roberts would not cancel her membership, even after
she mailed in doctors' notes informing the health club that she had
a heart problem. Her membership was canceled only after the
Department of Consumer Affairs got involved and a local television
station told her story.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just so glad it's over,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Under state law, Polonetsky said, ``If there is a physical
disability that keeps you from using the gym for six months, then
you're entitled to a refund'' for that period.
</P>
<P>
   The law also says that if you move 25 miles from the gym's
nearest location you are entitled to void the contract. Similarly,
you can void the contract if you change your mind about joining a
gym within three days of signing the contract.
</P>
<P>
   ``Lucille Roberts violated the law in their contracts, which
state that the contract can be canceled only if there is a
permanent disability,'' said Polonetsky, at a news conference. He
said complaints were also filed against Lucille Roberts by the
Better Business Bureau and the state attorney general's office.
</P>
<P>
   The management at Lucille Roberts could not be reached for
comment. Employees at four Manhattan branches said they did not
know how to get in touch with executives at the health club by
phone, and offered only a mailing address.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
